President Joseph R. Biden Jr. has submitted a notice to Congress stating that the national emergency declared in Executive Order 13873 on May 15, 2019, regarding securing the information and communications technology and services supply chain, will continue beyond May 15, 2021. The President emphasizes that the unrestricted acquisition or use of technology and services from foreign adversaries can create vulnerabilities that pose a significant threat to national security, foreign policy, and the economy of the United States. Therefore, the President has determined that it is necessary to extend the national emergency.